TY  - JOUR
T1  - Self-Interested Routing in Queueing Networks
AU  - Parlaktürk, Ali K.
AU  - Kumar, Sunil
Y1  - 2004/07/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1040.0251
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1040.0251
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 949
EP  - 966
VL  - 50
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We study self-interested routing in stochastic networks, taking into account the discrete stochastic dynamics of such networks. We analyze a two-station multiclass queueing network in which the system manager chooses the scheduling rule and individual customers choose routes in a self-interested manner. We show that this network can be unstable in Nash equilibrium under some scheduling rules. We also design a nontrivial scheduling rule that negates the performance degradation resulting from self-interested routing and achieves a Nash equilibrium with performance comparable to the first-best solution.
AB  - We study self-interested routing in stochastic networks, taking into account the discrete stochastic dynamics of such networks. We analyze a two-station multiclass queueing network in which the system manager chooses the scheduling rule and individual customers choose routes in a self-interested manner. We show that this network can be unstable in Nash equilibrium under some scheduling rules. We also design a nontrivial scheduling rule that negates the performance degradation resulting from self-interested routing and achieves a Nash equilibrium with performance comparable to the first-best solution.
